&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2919&quot; title=&quot;org.apache.fontbox.cff.CFFParser.readEntry sometimes throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2919&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2919&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: throw IOException instead of IllegalArgumentException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15413720" author="tilman" created="Tue, 9 Aug 2016 15:26:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Glyphs now appear blank in rendering. Adobe Reader and PDF.js do the same; GSView and IC*PDF display glyphs in another font. The cause in PDFBox is that the /WIDTHS entries are all 0. Bad widths are also the cause for the files in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3457&quot; title=&quot;Glyphs rendered in wrong width&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3457&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3457&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
